        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 1:16PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>The combination of low relative humidity and gusty winds will
create an increased risk for fire start and spread this afternoon
and evening.

We can expect relative humidity values as low as 25 to 35
percent, along with southwesterly winds of 10 to 20 mph with
gusts of 25 to 30 mph this afternoon. Higher wind gusts are
likely along the ridges.

These conditions could lead to the rapid spread of any fires that
do occur. Consult your local burn permitting authorities on
whether you may burn outdoors today. Virginia law prohibits
burning in the spring from midnight to 4PM...February 15th through
April 30th.
</description>
